== Install ==
'''This can lead to breaking the package upgrading system!''' This is because we are mixing Debian (which Whonix is based on) with Ubuntu software sources.

This is counter to best practices on the [[Install Software]] page. Therefore use a separate Whonix-Workstation.

Add Ubuntu's apt signing key.

{{CodeSelect|code=
sudo apt-key --keyring /etc/apt/trusted.gpg.d/ubuntu.gpg adv --keyserver hkp://qdigse2yzvuglcix.onion --recv-keys 630239CC130E1A7FD81A27B140976EAF437D05B5
}}

Expected output.

<pre>
Executing: /tmp/apt-key-gpghome.FJbIJCKlJf/gpg.1.sh --keyserver hkp://qdigse2yzvuglcix.onion --recv-keys 630239CC130E1A7FD81A27B140976EAF437D05B5
gpg: key 40976EAF437D05B5: public key "Ubuntu Archive Automatic Signing Key <ftpmaster@ubuntu.com>" imported
gpg: Total number processed: 1
gpg:               imported: 1
</pre>

<ref>
Created using 
https://repogen.simplylinux.ch/#
</ref> <ref>
https://me-download.wickr.com/#/version/me says Ubuntu 16.04 which is xenial.
</ref>

{{Open with root rights|filename=
/etc/apt/sources.list.d/ubuntu.list
}}

{{CodeSelect|code=
###### Ubuntu Main Repos
deb http://uk.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ xenial main 

###### Ubuntu Update Repos
deb http://uk.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ xenial-security main 
deb http://uk.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ xenial-updates main 
}}

{{Update}}

{{CodeSelect|code=
sudo apt-get update
}}

Install dependencies.

{{CodeSelect|code=
sudo apt-get install libhunspell-1.3 libprotobuf9v5
}}

Download WickrMe from https://me-download.wickr.com/#/version/me. <ref>
* https://wickr.com/
* https://support.wickr.com/hc/en-us/articles/115003136873-How-to-Install-on-Linux
</ref>

Save in <code>~/Downloads</code> folder. (Hint [[Tor Browser#Navigating Tor Browser Downloads]].)

Change to Downloads folder.

{{CodeSelect|code=
cd ~/Downloads
}}

Unzip.

{{CodeSelect|code=
unzip WickrMe-4.59.10.zip
}}

Install. <ref>
Replaced gdebi with dpkg. It's just a deb. Dpkg should be very very much fine. Even easier to debug than graphical frontend gdebi.
</ref>

Install WickrQt.

{{CodeSelect|code=
sudo dpkg -i wickr-qt_5.9.4_amd64.deb
}}

Install WickrMe.

{{CodeSelect|code=
sudo dpkg -i WickrMe_4.59.10-01_amd64.deb
}}

Fix dependencies.

{{CodeSelect|code=
sudo apt-get install -f
}}

Fix packaging conflict (since we mix with Ubuntu).

{{CodeSelect|code=
sudo dpkg --force-all --install libgstreamer-plugins-good1.0-0_1.8.3-1ubuntu0.4_amd64.deb
}}

The installation process is now complete.

